==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roric
<hw>Ro"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ros</ets>,
<ets>roris</ets>, dew.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to dew; resembling
dew; dewy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Roric figures</b></col> <fld>(Physics)</fld>, <cd>figures
which appear upon a polished surface, as glass, when objects which have
been near to, or in contact with, the surface are removed and the
surface breathed upon; -- called also <altname>Moser's
images</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rorid</ent>⟦br⟧
